column5: Watching might make you want to do it  <object width="425" height="355"><param name="movie" value="
Was a great day guys,and it only made it better by meeting new friends.....We'll probably see you again as we're heading that way this weekend.....TC and tight lines......Chuck....
Cool!   I was wondering about the thickness of the ice.  It looks pretty thin in the shots inside the hut.
Great job on the video, looks like a lot of fun out there...very nice fish
15 inches. The bottom is of the ice is the strong clear stuff.

It was a great day on the ice ...A few fish a few laughs and even got to meet some new fellow ofners which is always nice....sweet video Iceguy....really gets me excited for tomorrow morning....Gotta love those chunky simcoe whities
Wait. Lake Simcoe? Out by Barrie? I just started fishing there last September.  Hell, I gotta get me an ice fishing rig, and head up there!
yeah mcleod ....best time to get out there anf get some fish....ice is nice and tight and they were on today again
Awesome Report, thanks for the video.  Curious, where did you get the opening pic with all the people on lake simcoe from?
Nice work Rob - looking forward to next week.  :-)

I think its from Minnesota ice tourney. The pic is representing the crowds on Simcoe near shore. Thanks to all the great comments, Hope to make some more(ie underwater,perch/pike) I'm starting to get enough footage to make a "the one that got away"video and maybe some bloopers.
